JJ Peters (25) appeared in the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court this morning, March 2, as the accused in the murder of his grandmother, Susanna Kilmister (68), on February 28. Peters also appeared briefly in court on Tuesday March 1, when a confession he had made to a senior police official was confirmed. ALSO READ: Trial of former Mpumalanga MEC Mandla Msibi transferred to Mpumalanga High Court Kilmister was murdered in the early hours of February 28. She was apparently strangled, allegedly by Peters, who had been sharing her house on a smallholding in the Cromdale area about six kilometres outside the city on the R40. The matter was remanded to March 10 for a formal bail application. Read the full story in tomorrow’s Lowvelder.